description: Ever wonder who would win in court: Troll Dolls vs Furbies? Dunkaroos vs Gushers? Celine Dion vs Mariah Carey? Neither have we. UNTIL NOW. Two most excellent aspects of the 90s face off in court and have their sides presented by two experts: children of the 90s. Also featuring lots of other 90s nostalgic nonsense.

items.content:
This is it - the final episode of 90s Court! On this episode we drop all the things we always wanted to cover but couldn’t squeeze in in time. Listen for the biggest reminder of how much you loved the 90s! It has been amazing doing this show over the past 2.5 years. We thank you all for your support and listens. All we ask of you now is to stay rad.

To Celebrate the Launch of Andy's New Podcast "Anomalous Fascination", we are doing a feed drop in the 90s court feed. The episode is a quick listen, and you might even learn something new.  Also, for the first and probably LAST time ever in the 90s Court feed, there is an episode NOT marked explicit. If you like the show or want to hear more - check out Andy's Podcast @AnomalyPod on Twitter, and give them a subscribe on Spotify (still pending approval by other podcast apps).

In episode 1, we look upward, gazing at the stars above us and receiving more questions than answers. This weeks episode discusses an event in 1977 that was so incredible and unusual, that scientists still have no answers for how it happened. (please note that the 2017 findings, while compelling, have not been widely accepted by everyone and are discussed at the end of the episode).

Thank you to Blear Moon for the use of their songs "Watching Tower" and "Convert Congregation".  You can find more from them at http://secretpress.bandcamp.com.

And thank you to Sergey Cheremisinov for the use of their song "The Healing". You can find more from them at http://freemusicarchive.org/music/Sergey_Cheremisinov/The_Healing/The_Healing.

Sources: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wow!_signal and https://earthsky.org/space/wow-signal-explained-comets-antonio-paris
